</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-PROSECUTORS (Washington) _ The Republican congressmen
appointed as managers of President Clinton's impeachment trial in
the Senate have as many questions as answers about the historic
roles they are set to play. By Frank J. Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   CIVIL-LAW-SCHOOLS (Washington) _ Across the country, ``A Civil
Action,'' Jonathan Harr's 1995 best seller, is required reading in
courses in at least 50 law schools, including Harvard, Yale,
Columbia, Georgetown and here at American University. The book is
playing an extraordinary role in what some legal educators describe
as a movement to modernize the training of lawyers in America. By
William Glaberson.
</P>
