<P>
   HOLIDAY-TRAVEL (Undated) _ The holidays are a time for family
gatherings, but togetherness at Christmas does not have to be
confined to the home. In fact, because they are determined to
preserve family ties, a growing number of Americans can be found
huddling around Christmas trees in the lobbies of distant hotels,
or on cruise ships sailing the Caribbean. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
