   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   EURO-BANKERS (London) _ The euro, Europe's single currency,
makes its debut in just a week, creating a vast currency zone from
the Arctic Circle to the Mediterranean. And to listen to the most
optimistic of those seeking profit there, the currency's birth will
unlock a mother lode of wealth that has set U.S. investment banks
competing to export more of Wall Street's ways to continental
Europe. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
