<P>
   AGING-WRITERS (Los Angeles) _ Hollywood's obsession with youth
is freezing out many veteran writers over 40 from working on TV
and, to a lesser degree, on movies. We talk with writers who have
been forced to ditch what was once an exciting and lucrative career
and examine whether worshipping at the Fountain of Youth makes
financial sense for the studios and networks. By Dave McNary. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news file.)
