</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-GREENV27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Grrrowl a market success
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENVILLE, S.C. _ In his four years as co-owner of the ECHL's
Charlotte Checkers, Carl Scheer learned something foreign in
major-league sports: You don't have to excel on the ice to draw
fans; you just have to package properly.
</P>
<P>
   Welcome to Packaging Central.
</P>
<P>
   The name Greenville Grrrowl _ that's three R's _ was created by
an ad agency. The team plays in a new 14,000-seat, $64 million
arena, the Bi-Lo Center, which looks like an art museum from the
outside. Scheer orchestrated construction but took little financial
risk. The 30 luxury suites are sold out. There are 3,900
season-ticket holders, and games average 9,200, second-highest in
the ECHL. Scheer said he wouldn't sell the franchise, which he
purchased for $1 million dollars, for $5 million.
</P>
<P>
   If hockey seems secondary at Grrrowl games, it's not an
accident: players skating onto the ice through an inflatable
doghouse, twirling spotlights, the ``Grrrowl Girls'' dancing to
rock music, goofy games between periods.
</P>
<P>
   Should anyone not understand the sport, coach John Marks says,
``I tell people to look at hockey like they do basketball. They're
both five on five. There's transition from offense to defense. In
both, you're trying to take it to the net, and a hand check is just
like slashing, except that you're doing it with a five-foot
weapon.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Merchandising: Plentiful. Best may be the $6 puck with a bite
taken out of it.
</P>
<P>
   _ Nourishment: ``BBQ of the South'' pork sandwich; Blueplate
``Meat and 2'' for $6; Carolina Blonde Beer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Between periods: If you're not interested in on-ice games,
there is an autograph session in the lobby after the first period
with players not suited up.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best promotions: Coach does on-ice interview immediately after
the game for fans; ``Dog Obediance Class,'' a free pamphlet
explaining rules and penalties; box office phone number, 467-GRRR.
</P>
<P>
   _ Never thought you'd hear: On the Grrrowl's colorful Web site
(http://www.grrrowl.com), move the mouse over the team's logo and
hear the sound of a dog biting a puck. Move it to the ``Bad Dog''
icon and hear comedian Bill Murray say, ``You beast. You savage.
Come on, bark like a dog for me.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
