<P>
   HKN-HOCKEYBOOM _ ATLANTA _ Hockey has boomed across the South,
and we're not just talking about NHL franchises that have popped up
in Atlanta, Nashville, North Carolina, Tampa and Miami. Forty
hockey teams spread across the NHL and six different minor leagues
keep southern hockey fans occupied. Most are thriving, because of
low overhead (leagues have salary caps) and the game is a novelty
in Southern markets. The seeds are planted for the Thrashers'
success in Atlanta. (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 59.
