a new period of uncertainty, Zinni, who as commander of the U.S.
Central Command oversees all American forces from Sudan to
Pakistan, will play a major role. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NAPA, Calif. -- Dec. 26, 1998 -- CALIF-ART-SCHOOL, 12-26
-- Stephen Thomas, a printmaker, is the director of the Oxbow
School, a boarding school in a Victorian-style house in Napa, where
classes will be led by a teacher and an artist. The school's first
class, made up of 48 high school juniors drawn from private and
public high schools around the country, will arrive next September.
(Dan Krauss/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
